gov.usgs.volcanoes.swarm.data

Class WWSSource

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.volcanoes.swarm.data.SeismicDataSource
      • gov.usgs.volcanoes.swarm.data.WWSSource
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    RsamSource

    public class WWSSource
extends SeismicDataSource
implements RsamSource
    An implementation of SeismicDataSource that communicates with a WinstonWaveServer. This is essentially just a copy of WaveServerSource with different helicorder functions. It should probably be made a descendant of WaveServerSource.
    Author:
    Dan Cervelli

        public SeismicDataSource getCopy()
        Description copied from class: SeismicDataSource
        Get a copy of the data source. The default implementation returns an identical copy, that is, this. This is confusing. Why return a reference to an object the caller already has? Should this really return a clone? If so, why not call it clone()? --tjp
